  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency water, sanitation and hygiene (WASH) response to conflict-affected populations in Tigray Region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project this WASH response is to provide life-saving WASH services and supplies for the affected population, including children displaced due to the conflict in Tigray, reaching an anticipated 280,000 persons (directly). This UNICEF project provides freshwater supply through emergency water trucking and rehabilitation of water systems, construction of emergency latrines, building of handwashing facilities,  promotion of hygiene practices including risk communication and community education (RCCE) for COVID-19, and distribution of life-saving WASH NFI. The project provides life-saving assistance to 280,000 people, including 53,200 women, 47,600 men,179,200 children, and 47,600 people with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
